			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">What I have found to work best is to designate a HO starter. Generally a scout because they have more options and access to the higher tier HO's. Then if you have more then one of any class, designate one to work on the starter chain, and the other work on the combat wheel. 
<br />

<br />
I personally use a macro that says "HO starting in 3 seconds" before I start up the HO. I also scroll back a bit to see the group, it can help you see the priest trying to get off the last second heal. You can wait an additional second and everything goes smoothly.
<br />

<br />
We're working on a group and duo section to help people through the process of working with others. 
<br />

<br />
Keep the questions coming, the more people that understand about heroic opportunities the better <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
